name: Dr. Ruth Westheimer
summary: Dr. Ruth Westheimer, the renowned sex therapist and talk show host, has passed away at the age of 96. As "Dr. Ruth," she became an American icon, known for her diminutive stature and direct approach to discussing sexuality. Her decades-long career in sex therapy and media made a profound impact on generations, breaking down taboos and empowering individuals to communicate openly about intimate matters. Westheimer's life and work are celebrated as she is remembered for her significant contributions to sex education and the normalization of open dialogue about sexual health.

NASCAR conducted an investigation and delivered its verdict, raising questions about the severity of the fine.
